The All Progressives Congress (APC), on Saturday, took its presidential campaign to Dutse, Jigawa state. Bola Tinubu, flagbearer of the party, and Kashim Shettima, his running mate, were present at the rally. Also present were Mohammed Badaru, Jigawa governor, and Bello Matawalle of Zamfara. Senate President Ahmad Lawan and Femi Gbajabiamila, speaker of the house of representatives, were also in attendance. Below are photos:          